The system has the command format (it is required to upload to a server, due to the lack of a server, this plugin was not fully tested)
It has a save in MongoDB or .json files (if the MONGO_URL environment variable is undefined it will use the jsons system.)

It also has enough logic to generate summaries from the last one created or from scratch


1) First you have to generate the .env with the following fields:


generate .env with :

SLACK_BOT_TOKEN="TOKEN BOT SLACK"
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET="SIGNING SECRET SLACK"
CHAT_GPT_KEY="CHAT GTP KEY"
CHANNEL_NAME="CHANNEL NAME TO MAKE SUMMARY"
PORT=3000
MONGO_URL="URL MONGO" // optional if you want to save summaries in mongo


2) npm install


for local test: you can use 
 generateSummaryOffline(); /app.js

3) to start -> npm start

